      </prefercite>
      <bioghist id="aspace_d1f47642ac1e0a27101b72ab8c1af93a">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>William Vernon Brelsford was born in 1907 and educated at Oxford. He entered the colonial service in Northern Rhodesia (now Zambia) in 1930. He was named secretary-curator to establish the Rhodes-Livingstone Institute and Museum, 1937-1938; was acting information officer, 1945; acting director of Information, 1948; president of the Northern Rhodesia Society; editor of the Northern Rhodesia Journal, 1950-1965; director of Information, 1951; and director of the Federal Information Department, Federation of Rhodesia and Nyasaland, 1953-1960; and a member of the legislative assembly, 1962-1965. He is the author of many books on Northern Rhodesia.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_036331051f5bb0bc4bcf32293b4fa1c2">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The papers consist of correspondence, subject files, printed material, maps, and photographs relating to Northern Rhodesia (now Zambia) and Nyasaland (now Malawi). Compiled by William Vernon Brelsford.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
